(24, 2, 0, 1, 5, 0, 'Dietitian', 0, 0, 'â¢	Plan meals for the patients according to the diet prescription.\r\nâ¢	Supervise service of meals and feeds to the patients.\r\nâ¢	Assess Nutritional needs of patients.\r\nâ¢	Meet In-patients on daily basis to ensure their nutritional needs are met.\r\nâ¢	Modify meal plans according to the condition of the patient.\r\nâ¢	Get feedbacks from patients and satisfy their needs on the basis of their medical condition.\r\nâ¢	To work as a team with other staff, support staff and food service workers in ensuring patient satisfaction.    \r\nâ¢	Enforce and supervise sanitary and safety regulations during food service.\r\nâ¢	Prepare records and reports:- \r\nâ¢	Nutritional assessment within 24hrs of admission.\r\nâ¢	Nutritional re-assessment every 3rd day.\r\nâ¢	Plan diet recommendation to patients & order diet(through Supervisor)\r\nâ¢	Assure quality as per matrix.\r\n', 'â¢	Plan meals for the patients according to the diet prescription.\r\nâ¢	Supervise service of meals and feeds to the patients.\r\nâ¢	Assess Nutritional needs of patients.\r\nâ¢	Meet In-patients on daily basis to ensure their nutritional needs are met.\r\nâ¢	Modify meal plans according to the condition of the patient.\r\nâ¢	Get feedbacks from patients and satisfy their needs on the basis of their medical condition.\r\nâ¢	To work as a team with other staff, support staff and food service workers in ensuring patient satisfaction.    \r\nâ¢	Enforce and supervise sanitary and safety regulations during food service.\r\nâ¢	Prepare records and reports:- \r\nâ¢	Nutritional assessment within 24hrs of admission.\r\nâ¢	Nutritional re-assessment every 3rd day.\r\nâ¢	Plan diet recommendation to patients & order diet(through Supervisor)\r\nâ¢	Assure quality as per matrix.\r\n', 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0),
(25, 2, 0, 0, 7, 0, 'Nursing Superintendent ', 0, 0, 'Job Responsibilities:				\r\n					Rounds\r\nâ¢	During rounds she/he will converse with patients and family to ascertain any issues related to services of any kind and inform/liaise with other departments to resolve them.\r\nâ¢	She/ he will take 5 â 6 night rounds in a month.\r\nâ¢	Checks all pre-post and very sick patients for appropriate care.\r\n\r\nADMINISTRATION\r\nâ¢	Meets all new joinees of concerned area, orients them and ensures they are properly mentored by a senior nurse. Also send them for HR and Nursing Inductions as per schedule.\r\n\r\nâ¢	Take part in human resource planning. \r\n\r\nâ¢	 Hiring of nursing staff (interviewing)\r\n\r\nâ¢	MRD files (Ensure all the files reach MRD before nursing in-charge leave the duty.\r\n\r\nâ¢	Co- ordinate in the case of Non-availability of medicines.\r\n\r\nâ¢	Check the requirement of any equipment etc\r\n\r\nâ¢	Treats all internal and external customers with respect, fairness and concern for their welfare.\r\n\r\nâ¢	Foster effective professional relationships with other departments & all members. \r\n\r\nALLOCATION\r\nâ¢	Ensures enough staffing for 24 hrs. Liaise with shift supervisor for requirement of staff in his/ her own or other areas in case of less/more occupancy in the areas.\r\nâ¢	Ensures a trained or exp shift In-charge is placed in every shift.\r\nâ¢	 Conducts regular departmental meetings and addresses any unresolved issues.\r\nâ¢	Making rosters and any other assistance as required by the unit In-charge.\r\n\r\n INDUCTION TRAINING \r\n\r\nâ¢	Maintain department quality indicator report.\r\nâ¢	Checks if data of all quality indicators is collected appropriately. Ensures QI are sent on time in quality department. \r\nâ¢	Participates in unit or department Quality Improvement Program. Analyzes data to drive problem solving and process improvement activities.\r\nâ¢	Ensures reporting of any deviation from the set standards in the incident forms.\r\nâ¢	Ensures availability and adherence of departmental SOPâs and policies in her/his areas.\r\nâ¢	Educates and prepares staff on NABH Accreditation process.\r\n                                                            TRAINING\r\nâ¢	Encourages her staff to participate in the in-service education program conducted for nurses.\r\nâ¢	Performance test (Nursing staff for Appraisal )\r\nâ¢	Ensure classes are taken regularly\r\nâ¢	Project assigned to her/him.   \r\n', 'Job Responsibilities:				\r\n					Rounds\r\nâ¢	During rounds she/he will converse with patients and family to ascertain any issues related to services of any kind and inform/liaise with other departments to resolve them.\r\nâ¢	She/ he will take 5 â 6 night rounds in a month.\r\nâ¢	Checks all pre-post and very sick patients for appropriate care.\r\n\r\nADMINISTRATION\r\nâ¢	Meets all new joinees of concerned area, orients them and ensures they are properly mentored by a senior nurse. Also send them for HR and Nursing Inductions as per schedule.\r\n\r\nâ¢	Take part in human resource planning. \r\n\r\nâ¢	 Hiring of nursing staff (interviewing)\r\n\r\nâ¢	MRD files (Ensure all the files reach MRD before nursing in-charge leave the duty.\r\n\r\nâ¢	Co- ordinate in the case of Non-availability of medicines.\r\n\r\nâ¢	Check the requirement of any equipment etc\r\n\r\nâ¢	Treats all internal and external customers with respect, fairness and concern for their welfare.\r\n\r\nâ¢	Foster effective professional relationships with other departments & all members. \r\n\r\nALLOCATION\r\nâ¢	Ensures enough staffing for 24 hrs. Liaise with shift supervisor for requirement of staff in his/ her own or other areas in case of less/more occupancy in the areas.\r\nâ¢	Ensures a trained or exp shift In-charge is placed in every shift.\r\nâ¢	 Conducts regular departmental meetings and addresses any unresolved issues.\r\nâ¢	Making rosters and any other assistance as required by the unit In-charge.\r\n\r\