(26, 2, 0, 0, 7, 0, 'ICN', 0, 0, '1.	Daily visits to all the wards.\r\n2.	Collection and tabulation of daily data of incidence of hospital infection. Recorded data of all infections should include the type of infection, the cultures taken and the results (when known), any antibiotics administered, and the identity of the physician responsible for the patent.\r\n3.	Ensuring that the samples of blood, stool,sputum urine, swab-as the case may be-are collected and despatched to laboratory in time.\r\n4.	Provide the Infection control committee with written and oral reports concerning all infections within the hospital.\r\n5.	Document the Nosocomial Infections.\r\n6.	Compilation of ward wise, discipline wise or procedure wise statistics.\r\n7.	Daily visit to the laboratory to ascertain results of previous days samples.\r\n8.	Monitoring and supervision of infection among the hospital staff.\r\n9.	Report Occupational exposures of blood, body fluids, infectious materials and hazardous chemicals in accordance with the hospitalâs policies and procedures governing accidents and incidents. \r\n10.	Training of Nursing staff and paramedical personnel on Infection control practices.\r\n11.	Ensure proper segregation of biomedical waste.\r\n12.	Monitoring of process of CSSD like sterilization of equipments.\r\n\r\n', '1.	Daily visits to all the wards.\r\n2.	Collection and tabulation of daily data of incidence of hospital infection. Recorded data of all infections should include the type of infection, the cultures taken and the results (when known), any antibiotics administered, and the identity of the physician responsible for the patent.\r\n3.	Ensuring that the samples of blood, stool,sputum urine, swab-as the case may be-are collected and despatched to laboratory in time.\r\n4.	Provide the Infection control committee with written and oral reports concerning all infections within the hospital.\r\n5.	Document the Nosocomial Infections.\r\n6.	Compilation of ward wise, discipline wise or procedure wise statistics.\r\n7.	Daily visit to the laboratory to ascertain results of previous days samples.\r\n8.	Monitoring and supervision of infection among the hospital staff.\r\n9.	Report Occupational exposures of blood, body fluids, infectious materials and hazardous chemicals in accordance with the hospitalâs policies and procedures governing accidents and incidents. \r\n10.	Training of Nursing staff and paramedical personnel on Infection control practices.\r\n11.	Ensure proper segregation of biomedical waste.\r\n12.	Monitoring of process of CSSD like sterilization of equipments.\r\n\r\n', 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0),
