(35, 2, 0, 0, 9, 0, 'Emergency Medicine', 0, 0, '1.	Responsibility for the assessment and immediate care of all Emergency medicine patients attending the Emergency Department and linked units and personally supervise other clinical staff. \r\n2.	Responsibility for the care of patients admitted under the care of the Consultants in Emergency medicine to the Emergency Department, Clinical Decision Unit / EM Observation ward or Chest Pain Assessment Unit, if available on site. This entails daily ward rounds, including weekends and cross-cover of patient care on a pre-agreed or on-call basis. \r\n3.	To undertake essential supporting duties for clinical care including, inter alia, risk management, critical incident investigation and oversight of rosters.\r\n4.	To ensure that duties and functions are undertaken in a manner that minimizes delays for patients and possible disruption of services. \r\n5.	Ongoing participation in Major Incident Planning for the Emergency department and the hospital.\r\n6.	The selection, supervision and training of Medical officer and the allocation of duties to them. \r\n7.	Contribute to the provision of structured training and situational learning opportunities for Medical officers on recognized training programmes and support the clinical and professional development of medical staff in the Emergency Department. \r\n8.	Provide training and clinical support, if requested, to non-medical clinical staff in the Emergency Department including Nursing staff and other healthcare providers.\r\n9.	The supervision of students in medical, nursing and allied health professions assigned to the ED.\r\n10.	To formally review the execution of the Clinical Services with the Clinical Director / Employer periodically. The Clinical Directorate Service Plan shall be reviewed periodically at the request of the Consultant or Clinical Director / Employer. The Consultant may initially seek internal review of the determinations of the Clinical Director regarding the Service Plan.\r\n11.	To participate in the Clinical Directorate structure. The Consultant shall receive training and support to enable him/her to participate fully in such structures. \r\n12.	Participate in the collection, analysis and the reporting of data necessary for quality assurance activities in the Emergency Department and for other hospital.\r\n13.	Engage in audit activity and provide leadership audit in the Emergency Department.\r\n14.	Promote effective team working within the Emergency Department. \r\n15.	Ensuring optimal communication with all medical, management and support services in the hospital, with General Practitioners, Community Care Services and with external agencies relevant to emergency care. \r\n16.	Participation in the selection of medical staff and, as appropriate, other staff involved in service provision the Emergency Department.\r\n17.	Actively engage in Continuing Professional Development and comply with Professional Competence Assurance requirements. The above Job Description is not intended to be a comprehensive list of all duties involved and consequently, the post holder may be required to perform other duties as appropriate to the post and in keeping with development of the post through scheduled review of the Consultantâs job plan with the Clinical Director.\r\n', '1.	Responsibility for the assessment and immediate care of all Emergency medicine patients attending the Emergency Department and linked units and personally supervise other clinical staff. \r\n2.	Responsibility for the care of patients admitted under the care of the Consultants in Emergency medicine to the Emergency Department, Clinical Decision Unit / EM Observation ward or Chest Pain Assessment Unit, if available on site. This entails daily ward rounds, including weekends and cross-cover of patient care on a pre-agreed or on-call basis. \r\n3.	To undertake essential supporting duties for clinical care including, inter alia, risk management, critical incident investigation and oversight of rosters.\r\n4.	To ensure that duties and functions are undertaken in a manner that minimizes delays for patients and possible disruption of services. \r\n5.	Ongoing participation in Major Incident Planning for the Emergency department and the hospital.\r\n6.	The selection, supervision and training of Medical officer and the allocation of duties to them. \r\n7.	Contribute to the provision of structured training and situational learning opportunities for Medical officers on recognized training programmes and support the clinical and professional development of medical staff in the Emergency Department. \r\n8.	Provide training and clinical support, if requested, to non-medical clinical staff in the Emergency Department including Nursing staff and other healthcare providers.\r\n9.	The supervision of students in medical, nursing and allied health professions assigned to the ED.\r\n10.	To formally review the execution of the Clinical Services with the Clinical Director / Employer periodically. The Clinical Directorate Service Plan shall be reviewed periodically at the request of the Consultant or Clinical Director / Employer. The Consultant may initially seek internal review of the determinations of the Clinical Director regarding the Service Plan.\r\n11.	To participate in the Clinical Directorate structure. The Consultant shall receive training and support to enable him/her to participate fully in such structures. \r\n12.	Participate in the collection, analysis and the reporting of data necessary for quality assurance activities in the Emergency Department and for other hospital.\r\n13.	Engage in audit activity and provide leadership audit in the Emergency Department.\r\n14.	Promote effective team working within the Emergency Department. \r\n15.	Ensuring optimal communication with all medical, management and support services in the hospital, with General Practitioners, Community Care Services and with external agencies relevant to emergency care. \r\n16.	Participation in the selection of medical staff and, as appropriate, other staff involved in service provision the Emergency Department.\r\n17.	Actively engage in Continuing Professional Development and comply with Professional Competence Assurance requirements. The above Job Description is not intended to be a comprehensive list of all duties involved and consequently, the post holder may be required to perform other duties as appropriate to the post and in keeping with development of the post through scheduled review of the Consultantâs job plan with the Clinical Director.\r\n', 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0),
(36, 2, 0, 1, 9, 0, 'Consultant', 0, 0, 'â¢Perform routine checkups of patients.\r\nKeep detailed notes of the patient checkup. \r\nPerform diagnostic tests to diagnose patients.\r\nProvide quality healthcare to patients. \r\nTake part in further education opportunities. \r\nCreate a care plan for a patient. \r\nShall be responsible for diagnosis and treatment of all cases pertaining to the patients and must be available to examine and consult/advise on any particular case, if request by any of his/her colleagues. \r\nShall call, when required, other specialists to help in arriving at a correct decision making a diagnosis and charting out the treatment. \r\nShall attend promptly to acutely ill patients and make arrangements for immediate admission. If, however, beds are not available for such patients, they should be promptly referred to a proper medical Centre.\r\nShall maintain patients\' records correctly and take proper care of the patients.\r\nShall instruct and guide staff nurse to the proper medical techniques and treatment.\r\n\r\n', 'Perform routine checkups of patients.\r\nKeep detailed notes of the patient checkup. \r\nPerform diagnostic tests to diagnose patients.\r\nProvide quality healthcare to patients. \r\nTake part in further education opportunities. \r\nCreate a care plan for a patient. \r\nShall be responsible for diagnosis and treatment of all cases pertaining to the patients and must be available to examine and consult/advise on any particular case, if request by any of his/her colleagues. \r\nShall call, when required, other specialists to help in arriving at a correct decision making a diagnosis and charting out the treatment. \r\nShall attend promptly to acutely ill patients and make arrangements for immediate admission. If, however, beds are not available for such patients, they should be promptly referred to a proper medical Centre.\r\nShall maintain patients\' records correctly and take proper care of the patients.\r\nShall instruct and guide staff nurse to the proper medical techniques and treatment.\r\n\r\n', 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 0);
